channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Domino's will tip you if you tip your driver
Wall Street stands by Meta even as costs rise and the stock sells off, cites AI leadership
item.description: Wall Street analysts are standing by Meta Platforms despite Thursday's sell-off.

item.title: High interest rates catch up to economic growth as GDP slows dramatically to 1.6%
item.description: Consumers kept spending at a solid pace, but overall, the economy's “momentum is cooling," said one economist.

item.title: New Taylor Swift song resonates with working women: ‘I cry a lot but I am so productive, it's an art'
item.description: A lyric from Taylor Swift's "I Can Do It With a Broken Heart," on her new "Tortured Poets Department" album, is resonating with many working women on TikTok.

item.title: Sam Altman’s Worldcoin eyeing partnerships with PayPal and OpenAI
item.description: Tools for Humanity has dropped hints it soon could be collaborating with major tech and finance companies, despite a declining rate of new users.

item.title: Dow drops more than 600 points on inflation and growth concerns, heads for biggest drop of the year: Live updates
item.description: Stocks fell sharply Thursday after the latest U.S. economic data showed a sharp slowdown in growth and pointed to persistent inflation.

item.title: PBS Retro brings back your childhood favorite shows
item.description: Options include Mister Rogers Neighborhood, Zoboomafoo and Reading Rainbow.

item.title: Open seating no more? Southwest CEO says airline is weighing cabin changes
item.description: Southwest stands apart from other large airlines because it does not have seat assignments.

item.title: Movement Labs raises $38 million to build layer 2 blockchain on Ethereum with Facebook tech
item.description: Polychain led the Series A funding round, which included participation from Hack VC, dao5, and Robot Ventures.

item.title: Honda to build $11 billion electric vehicle hub in Canada
item.description: Honda and its joint venture partners plan to invest $11 billion in Ontario, Canada to create a "comprehensive EV value chain," the Japanese automaker announced.
